29/12/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO Senior Military Representative to Skopje David Humar handed over the keys to the Camp Able Sentry to the Macedonian army on Tuesday (December 28th). 
The facility had accommodated NATO's Headquarters in Skopje. 
NATO's advisory team is moving now to the premises of the defence ministry. 
Macedonian Defence Minister Zoran Konjanovski said that the handover symbolises Macedonia's maturity and readiness. 
Humar said that the step confirms the country has achieved significant progress in security and defence reforms. 
(MIA, Kanal 5, Makfax - 28/12/10)
